# planning-canonical-package-check-nonlibrary-repo — History

## v1.1.0 (2026-07-03)

**Changed by:** Myrmidons issue #749 planning — "Add canonical `package` CI check" for an
agent-manifest/dataset repo (plan-only; nothing executed).

**Verification:** unverified (both versions are PLAN-only; no CI has validated either job YAML).

### What changed (minor bump 1.0.0 → 1.1.0 — additive, core workflow unchanged)

- Added a "Variant: manifest/dataset repo with a hardened workflow" section (Detailed Steps 7–12):
  1. When a canonical category "seems N/A", fetch the convention doc FIRST — Odysseus defines
     `package` as "sdist/wheel, container image, or release archive", so a dataset repo's release
     archive is a REAL distributable; the doc has no N/A marker and the board is generated from
     live check-runs on `main`, so "document as N/A" is a dead end.
  2. Check-run name = the job's `name:` field; the job must live in a workflow triggering on both
     `pull_request` and `push: branches: [main]` or the board cell stays empty.
  3. Mirror the nearest sibling repo's canonical job shape (org-wide `gh api search/code` for
     `filename:_required.yml`; ProjectHermes precedent with `needs: build`, SHA-pinned
     upload-artifact, `if-no-files-found: error`).
  4. Real teeth: deterministic GNU tar flags, SHA256SUMS, round-trip verify (extract + `diff -r`
     + non-zero file count + `sha256sum --check`).
  5. Read the hardened workflow's policy-guard jobs first (Myrmidons `forbid-suppressions`
     rejects `|| true`, `continue-on-error: true`, `::warning::`; `::error::` is permitted).
  6. Sync all documented homes of the required-check list; branch-protection registration is a
     manual POST-merge step.
- Added 3 Failed Attempts rows: documenting `package` as N/A; hosting the job in a PR-only
  workflow; registering the context in branch protection in the same PR.
- Results & Parameters: added the deterministic release-archive job YAML and a v1.1.0
  risks/uncertain-assumptions list (doc/precedent drift, unverified SHA pin, GNU-tar-only flags,
  plan unexecuted).
- Added Quick Reference commands 5–8; extended description/tags/When-to-Use; added a Verified On
  row for HomericIntelligence/Myrmidons #749.

### Why

A second plan-only session (Myrmidons #749) hit the same canonical-`package` problem shape on a
different non-library repo type (agent-manifest dataset) and produced durable, transferable
learnings — especially the "fetch the convention doc before assuming N/A" and "board reads
check-runs on main" rules — that belong in this skill rather than a near-duplicate new one.

